PERTH (miningweekly.com) – Junior Great Southern Mining has been granted a mining licence for its Southern Star project, in Western Australia, bridging another hurdle to the start of production. The mining lease has an initial term of 21 years. “Securing the grant of the mining lease is a pivotal moment for Great Southern Mining. It highlights the potential of Southern Star and is another step towards future mining activities in the larger Duketon gold project area,” said executive chairperson John Terpu. “The team has worked exceptionally hard since we acquired the Southern Star exploration licence and with the current reverse circulation programme over halfway complete, we eagerly await the results and are looking forward to updating the market on the company’s progression of the project.”